2004: A major earthquake off the west coast of Aceh Province, Indonesia, in northern Sumatra, on December 26 triggered a tsunami that struck 14 countries and killed 226,000 people on the coast of the Indian Ocean, more than half of them in Aceh.
2005: In March and early April, several strong earthquakes hit the west coast of Sumatra.
