2006: A 6.8-degree earthquake struck the south of Indonesia's most populated island of Java, triggering a tsunami that struck the south coast and killed nearly 700 people.
2009: An area near Padang, the capital of Western Sumatra province, is hit by a 7.6-degree earthquake.
More than 1,100 people died.
2010: A 7.5-degree earthquake struck one of the Sumatran islands – Mentawai Island, triggering a tsunami up to 10 meters high that destroyed dozens of villages and killed about 300 people.
